Prosecutors said Frank was the victim of the fastest-growing crime in America: identity theft.
``Identity theft is a plague right now,'' said Beth Givens of the Privacy Rights Clearinghouse in San Diego, which tracks the problem nationally
``Identity theft is the fastest-growing crime in America, maybe even the world,'' Los Angeles County District Attorney Gil Garcetti said at a news conference Wednesday to explain the new law
``The police just don't have time to really go after these problems,'' said Joanne Mankiewicz of San Francisco, whose name was used to amass $80,000 in debt
Identity theft is a crime that evolves with every advance in technology.
Santner and Shay participated in nearly every form of identity theft, the police said.
